tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE influencers (influencer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), followers INT, category VARCHAR(50));

CREATE TABLE user_interactions (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, influencer_id INT, interaction_type VARCHAR(50), interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP);

CREATE TABLE Posts (
    post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    influencer_id INT,
    post_content TEXT,
    post_date TIMESTAMP,
    likes_count INT,
    comments_count INT
);

CREATE TABLE Interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    post_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_date TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE post (
  post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  influencer_id INT,
  post_content TEXT,
  post_likes INT,
  post_comments INT,
  post_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (influencer_id) REFERENCES influencer(influencer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_interaction (
  interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  post_id INT,
  user_id INT,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(20),
  interaction_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (post_id) REFERENCES post(post_id)
);
